        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down. | Bromley. | Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Aug. 29<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>On my return home after a two months’ absence in Devonshire,<ref target="#foot.f2"/> on Tuesday night I found lying here the “Survey of Human Progress”,<ref target="#foot.f3"/> which you have very kindly sent me. I fear it has been lying here for some time. I am very glad to see that you have kept your intention of publishing on this grand &amp; interesting subject &amp; I hope in a few days to read your work.<ref target="#foot.f4"/></p>
<p>I thank you sincerely for sending me a copy &amp; with much respect, I [ … ] remain My dear Sir | Yours sincerely | Charles Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
                <div type="tnotes">
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.2 here] <hi rend="italic">corrected from</hi> ‘there’</note>
                </div>

            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the reference to CD’s stay in Devon and by the date of publication of Arnott’s book (see nn. 2 and 3, below).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD was in Torquay, Devon, during July and August 1861 (see <hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 9, Appendix II).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_228.xml" resp="#automat" cert="low">Arnott 1861</ref> was published in August 1861 (<hi rend="italic">Publishers’ Circular</hi>, 15 August 1861, p. 373).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">After receiving a pamphlet from Arnott on human progress, CD had encouraged him to write a book on the subject (see <hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 8, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-2677.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to Neil Arnott, 16 February [1860?]</ref> and n. 3).</note>
        </div>        
            
